  "texts": [
    "In parallel, multi-task learning has gained traction as a strategy to improve classification robustness and efficiency.",
    "By training models on related tasks, such as segmentation and classification, researchers can leverage shared representations, thereby reducing the amount of labeled data required.",
    "This approach is particularly beneficial for fossil classification, where labeled data can be scarce, and robust model performance is essential.",
    "Despite these advancements, challenges persist.",
    "Class imbalance continues to pose a significant hurdle, as the uneven fossil record can skew model performance toward overrepresented taxa."
  ],
